ce":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in good or perfect condition"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be honest, to be upright"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suit, respond, answer the purpose, be adequate","examples":[{"text":"11 Century CE, Wallada bint al-Mustakfi, أنا واللّه أصلح للمعالي\nأَنَا وَ الْلَّهِ أَصْلُحُ لِلْمَعَالِي ، وَأَمْشِي مِشْيَتِي وَأَتِيهُ تِيهَا\nʔanā wa l-llahi ʔaṣluḥu lilmaʕālī , waʔamšī mišyatī waʔatīhu tīhā\nI am, by Allah, adequate for high positions. And am going my way, with pride."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be righteous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in good or perfect condition"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be honest, to be upright"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fix, mend, improve","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reconciliation","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنِ ٱمْرَأَةٌ خَافَتْ مِن بَعْلِهَا نُشُوزًا أَوْ إِعْرَاضًا فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْهِمَا أَن يُصْلِحَا بَيْنَهُمَا صُلْحًا وَٱلصُّلْحُ خَيْرٌ","english":"And if a woman fears from her husband any inharmony or rebuffing, there is no blame on them if they reconcile. Indeed, reconciliation is good!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peace"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From صَلَحَ (ṣalaḥa, “to be right; to be adequate; to be sound, to be whole etc.”). Possibly influenced by Aramaic סָלַח (sālaḥ, “to forgive”)."},"ipa":null}